STATE of Iowa, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Marc Aaron HANSLIP, Defendant-Appellant. No. 17-1472 Court of Appeals of Iowa. Filed January 9, 2019

DECISION WITHOUT PUBLISHED OPINION See Iowa R. App. P. 6.904

The defendant appeals his convictions for being a felon in possession of a firearm and possession of an offensive weapon, both enhanced by the defendant's status as an habitual offender. AFFIRMED.

AFFIRMED.
